						               													<description>In Gold Nuggets you are collecting gold from streams and rivers - as well as from the other players!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn, roll 7 dice (sides: gold nugget, lasso, 2, 3, 4, 5). Then do the following:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a) Roll again, but before that, freeze at least one die:&amp;#10;- one or more lassoes, and/or&amp;#10;- one or more gold nuggets, and/or&amp;#10;- three or more numbered dice showing the same number. When 3 or more numbered dice are already frozen, you can freeze further dice (1 or more) of that number after the subsequent rolls.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;b) If you can't freeze any dice, you can't take any gold nuggets and your turn ends.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;c) If you decide to take the gold nuggets, you receive the following:&amp;#10;- 1 nugget for each die showing gold nuggets, and/or&amp;#10;- 2/3/4/5 nuggets for 3 or more dice showing the numbers 2/3/4/5, and/or&amp;#10;- if you have 3 lassoes, you can take gold nuggets from other players instead of taking it from the common stock.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you managed to use all seven dice then you get to take another turn!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once all the gold nuggets are gone from the middle, the game ends. The player with the most gold nuggets wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
